WEBVTT

00:01.669 --> 00:03.936
Joe, you're going to see
your first snow.

00:03.937 --> 00:07.339
It's so exciting!
I can't wait
to make a snow person!

00:07.341 --> 00:08.507
"Person"?

00:08.509 --> 00:10.609
We got to get him
out of that hippie school.

00:10.611 --> 00:11.777
I don't know, Jay.

00:11.779 --> 00:14.146
Last report card,
he got straight dolphins.

00:14.148 --> 00:16.882
Christmas in Colombia
was always hot and loud,

00:16.884 --> 00:19.952
people arguing,
betrayal, schemes.

00:19.954 --> 00:22.788
So I rented a Mountain cabin
for the whole family

00:22.790 --> 00:25.524
to celebrate my first Christmas
as an American.

00:25.526 --> 00:27.493
I want a white Christmas,

00:27.495 --> 00:30.462
you know,
like white people have.

00:30.464 --> 00:32.296
Hey, want to hit
the pipe one more time

00:32.299 --> 00:33.565
before
we get on the road?

00:33.567 --> 00:35.300
Um, yeah.
Couldn't hurt.

00:35.302 --> 00:37.036
[ Clears throat ]
[ Note plays ]

00:37.038 --> 00:39.972
Both: ♪ silent night ♪

00:39.974 --> 00:42.074
♪ holy night ♪

00:42.076 --> 00:43.509
Oh, my God,
we are killing it!

00:43.511 --> 00:46.378
Last Christmas, Mitchell and I
thought it would be fun

00:46.380 --> 00:48.747
to sing a little Christmas Carol
for the family.

00:48.749 --> 00:50.582
[ Inhales deeply ]
Unfortunately, it didn't go

00:50.584 --> 00:54.620
so well because somebody had
a little too much to drink.

00:56.490 --> 00:58.157
Stop doing that.
I was nervous.

00:58.159 --> 01:00.826
Both:
♪ 'tis the season to be jolly ♪

01:00.828 --> 01:03.495
♪ fa LA-LA, LA-LA,
LA-LA, LA, LA ♪

01:03.497 --> 01:06.331
♪ don we now our gay apparel ♪

01:06.333 --> 01:08.000
♪ fa LA-LA, LA-LA, LA-LA ♪

01:08.002 --> 01:09.001
[ Thud ]
Mitchell?

01:09.003 --> 01:10.169
[ Groans ]
[ Laughter ]

01:10.171 --> 01:12.838
The family has been mocking us
relentlessly all year.

01:12.840 --> 01:14.773
Nicknames
like screeches & herb,

01:14.775 --> 01:17.076
Simon & God-awful,
nickelback.

01:17.078 --> 01:18.944
But we're gonna
redeem ourselves this year.

01:18.946 --> 01:21.213
We have been rehearsing
our new number for months,

01:21.215 --> 01:23.682
and we will debut it
at the cabin

01:23.684 --> 01:26.618
as a special holiday "screw you"
to the family.

01:26.620 --> 01:28.287
Hey, Marty, listen,

01:28.289 --> 01:31.090
it's your hotel,
but a walnut closet

01:31.092 --> 01:33.192
is a place your guests want
to hang their clothes.

01:33.194 --> 01:35.761
A particleboard closet --
they want to hang themselves.

01:35.763 --> 01:38.097
All this closet stuff
is driving me nuts.
[ Door closes ]

01:38.099 --> 01:39.465
I want to get annoyed,

01:39.467 --> 01:41.266
but it's hard when I feel
this comfortable.

01:41.268 --> 01:43.302
Oh, God, he's gonna talk about
his new coat again.

01:43.304 --> 01:46.038
It's like getting a big,
warm hug from a mama sheep.

01:46.040 --> 01:47.940
Nothing feels
like pure sheepskin.

01:47.942 --> 01:49.274
The gal at the store said

01:49.276 --> 01:51.143
I looked
like kris kristofferson.

01:51.145 --> 01:52.478
We don't know who that is.

01:52.480 --> 01:54.079
[ Scoffs ] I have
so much lab homework

01:54.081 --> 01:55.647
to get done
during this break.

01:55.649 --> 01:57.116
If it were up to me,

01:57.118 --> 01:59.551
Christmas wouldn't
even come this year.

01:59.553 --> 02:01.887
Any chance you could sound more
like a cartoon villain?

02:01.889 --> 02:05.424
Come on, Alex, it's three
solid days of winter fun.

02:05.426 --> 02:07.392
We're gonna go sledding,
skating,

02:07.394 --> 02:09.228
ice-fishing,
make snow angels.

02:09.229 --> 02:11.630
Who's with me?!
[ Chanting ] Snow, snow!

02:11.632 --> 02:15.567
Together:
[ Chanting ] Snow, snow, snow,
snow, snow, snow, snow!

02:15.569 --> 02:17.236
Snow?

02:17.238 --> 02:18.837
No, that's a leaf.

02:18.839 --> 02:20.405
It's hotter here
than at home.

02:20.407 --> 02:21.940
Gloria,
in your little daily e-mails,

02:21.942 --> 02:23.275
you said
it was gonna be cold.

02:23.277 --> 02:24.743
That's what my phone said.

02:24.745 --> 02:26.912
-You're on celsius.
-Oh.

02:26.914 --> 02:29.581
It's going to be hot,
guys!

02:29.583 --> 02:32.651
--<font color="#ffff00"> Captions by vitac</font> --

02:38.592 --> 02:40.759
♪♪

02:42.029 --> 02:44.530
Oh, is the furnace on?!

02:44.532 --> 02:45.864
Phil,
take off that jacket.

02:45.866 --> 02:47.766
You're making me hot
just looking at you.

02:47.768 --> 02:49.535
Saleslady said
that would happen.

02:49.537 --> 02:51.537
Trust me, I'm cool as cucumber.

02:51.539 --> 02:54.273
Something about the coat
just knows what my body needs.

02:54.275 --> 02:55.941
You're sweating
like a heroin addict.

02:55.943 --> 02:58.944
Oh, hey, look, a piano.

02:58.946 --> 03:01.680
Maybe we can get a little song
from the crapenters.

03:04.952 --> 03:06.552
-Hey.
-Be cool.

03:06.554 --> 03:07.953
Andy's fiancée, Beth,
has to work,

03:07.955 --> 03:09.321
so Gloria invited him
for Christmas,

03:09.323 --> 03:11.223
which [Inhales sharply]
is complicated

03:11.225 --> 03:13.892
because we've been having sex
and nobody knows about it.

03:13.894 --> 03:16.128
I mean, we know.

03:16.130 --> 03:17.863
My family
cannot find out about us.

03:17.865 --> 03:19.464
I'm certainly not
gonna tell them.

03:19.466 --> 03:20.866
<i> I</i> still have
their respect.

03:20.868 --> 03:23.468
Andy, chop-chop.
Joe's making his bathroom face.

03:23.470 --> 03:25.804
All right, let's just go home.
I mean, it's hot.

03:25.806 --> 03:28.807
There's no wi-fi.
-Alex, stop being the grinch.

03:28.809 --> 03:32.377
If that is the worst problem,
then merry Christmas.

03:32.379 --> 03:34.146
Oh, thank God you made it!

03:34.148 --> 03:37.916
I thought you'd gotten
into a horrible car accident!

03:37.918 --> 03:39.384
Wait a second.

03:39.386 --> 03:42.521
You're not trip, tad, Lois,
Darcy, and Marlene.

03:42.523 --> 03:44.723
-No, we're other names.
-Who are you?

03:44.725 --> 03:46.158
Fig Wilson.

03:46.160 --> 03:48.527
My family's been coming here
for the holidays for years.

03:48.529 --> 03:50.529
We rented this cabin
from the Wilsons.

03:50.531 --> 03:52.831
They are in Hawaii.
-Nobody told me that.

03:52.833 --> 03:55.334
Okay, well, bye-bye.

03:55.336 --> 03:56.935
How could they abandon me?

03:56.937 --> 03:59.104
Uh, I'm the most caring one
in the family.

03:59.106 --> 04:01.006
I warn them about cancer.

04:01.008 --> 04:04.276
I buy their fat kids clothes
in aspirational sizes.

04:04.278 --> 04:07.012
I invite them all
to my dogs' funerals.

04:07.014 --> 04:09.181
Last one ran straight
into traffic.

04:09.183 --> 04:10.515
I can see that.

04:10.517 --> 04:12.251
Is it possible
the invitation got lost?

04:12.253 --> 04:14.786
I mean...
You seem great.

04:14.788 --> 04:18.790
Well, I guess I'll just get
my bags and walk down the hill.

04:18.791 --> 04:21.959
Hopefully, I'll get to the
bus station before nightfall.

04:21.962 --> 04:24.196
It's wolf season.

04:24.198 --> 04:26.365
Why don't you stay here
with us?

04:26.367 --> 04:28.033
It's Christmas.

04:28.035 --> 04:29.735
Oh.

04:29.737 --> 04:31.036
First time I saw you,

04:31.038 --> 04:33.105
I thought you were
gonna be a pain in the ass,

04:33.107 --> 04:36.041
but it turns out
you're my favorite.

04:36.043 --> 04:37.276
[ Chuckles ]

04:39.880 --> 04:42.214
[ Door rattling ]

04:42.216 --> 04:44.049
What do you think's
in here?

04:44.051 --> 04:46.952
No one told you the legend
of the forgotten boy?

04:46.954 --> 04:50.222
Happened right here
100 years ago.

04:50.224 --> 04:52.324
A boy was very bad,

04:52.326 --> 04:55.594
and his parents locked him
in this secret room

04:55.596 --> 04:57.462
and left him here
forever.

04:57.464 --> 04:59.164
They say at night,
you can hear him

04:59.166 --> 05:00.999
trying
to scratch his way out.

05:01.001 --> 05:02.401
[ Scratching ]

05:02.403 --> 05:03.969
We got her.

05:03.971 --> 05:06.738
[ Both chuckle ]
Idiots.

05:06.740 --> 05:08.674
That was you scratching,
right?

05:09.476 --> 05:11.410
-Oh.
-Oh, sorry.

05:11.412 --> 05:13.445
-No, you go.
-No, it's okay. After you.

05:13.447 --> 05:15.347
Here, I'll just...

05:15.349 --> 05:17.983
Oh, why don't I go...

05:17.985 --> 05:20.819
What are you guys doing --
having a staring contest?

05:20.821 --> 05:21.920
I got winners!

05:21.922 --> 05:24.156
Later, though.
Come here.

05:24.158 --> 05:25.791
Andy...

05:25.793 --> 05:27.492
I've got a very special
present for you.

05:27.494 --> 05:30.295
Did this guy tell you he passed
his real-estate-license test?

05:30.297 --> 05:31.530
I know.
I helped him cram.

05:31.532 --> 05:34.032
Ah, she's really
drilling me pretty hard.
Cool.

05:34.034 --> 05:36.201
Listen, when I first
got into real estate,

05:36.203 --> 05:38.337
I worked at one of those
big firms with the blazers.

05:38.339 --> 05:39.805
I'd rather
not say their name,

05:39.807 --> 05:41.673
but it rhymed with
"century not very fun."

05:41.675 --> 05:44.676
Anyway, I saved this.

05:44.678 --> 05:46.511
I'd like for you
to have it.

05:46.513 --> 05:47.813
Wow.
[ Chuckles ]

05:47.815 --> 05:50.649
When you wear it, remember
the values of our profession --

05:50.651 --> 05:53.985
trust, honor, integrity,
fidelity, and purity.

05:53.987 --> 05:55.354
[ Inhales deeply ]

05:55.356 --> 05:57.322
Are you worthy
of the blazer, Andy?

05:57.324 --> 05:58.623
-[ Sighs ]
-I want to be.

05:58.625 --> 06:00.826
I didn't expect it
to hit this hard.

06:00.828 --> 06:01.893
Me either.

06:01.895 --> 06:03.695
[ Crying ]

06:03.697 --> 06:05.997
Who wants eggnog?

06:05.999 --> 06:07.065
I'll take some.

06:07.067 --> 06:08.667
I had a tough week
at work.

06:08.669 --> 06:11.470
What do you do?
Oh, my dad and I are
in the closet business.

06:11.472 --> 06:14.339
I'm sorry, it almost
sounded like you said,
"closet business."

06:14.341 --> 06:17.709
I did -- residential and
hospitality storage solutions.

06:17.711 --> 06:19.177
Yikes.

06:19.179 --> 06:21.513
[ Sighs ] Hey, specks,
I'm dying over there.

06:21.515 --> 06:22.547
What are you reading?

06:22.549 --> 06:24.049
Science stuff.
I'm sure it'll bore you.

06:24.051 --> 06:26.218
I teach astrophysics
at m.I.T.

06:26.220 --> 06:27.586
Wait a minute.

06:27.588 --> 06:29.554
Are you f.N. Wilson?
-F-n right, I am!

06:29.556 --> 06:31.189
We just read your essay
on how solar flares

06:31.191 --> 06:32.691
will wipe out life
on earth!

06:32.693 --> 06:35.060
Hopefully before closet lady
corners me again.
[ Chuckles ]

06:35.062 --> 06:36.828
Hey, hey,
everybody's here,

06:36.830 --> 06:39.598
so let's just casually
make our way over to the piano.
Okay, okay.

06:39.600 --> 06:41.333
Ooh, what are we drinking there,
miss Scarlet?

06:41.335 --> 06:43.668
Relax. It's hot tea
for my throat.

06:43.670 --> 06:45.537
Oh, we should
have lily film us.

06:45.539 --> 06:47.172
-Oh, yeah.
-Hey, lily, come here.

06:47.174 --> 06:49.741
Okay, so, daddy and I are about
to sing a Christmas song, and --

06:49.743 --> 06:51.243
-I'm gonna stop you right there.
-No, no.

06:51.245 --> 06:52.544
No, it's not gonna be
like last year

06:52.546 --> 06:55.881
because we're prepared and
we're singing "silent night."

06:55.883 --> 06:57.916
That's my favorite.
Can I sing with you?

06:57.918 --> 06:59.584
Both: ♪ um ♪

06:59.586 --> 07:01.019
Aaaaaah!

07:01.021 --> 07:02.587
Both: Oh.

07:02.589 --> 07:05.524
[ Glass clinking ]
Can I have
everyone's attention, please?

07:05.526 --> 07:09.027
I feel so lucky
celebrating

07:09.029 --> 07:11.530
with the best damn family
any man could hope for.

07:11.532 --> 07:12.864
-Aww!
-Dad.

07:12.866 --> 07:14.933
-And fig.
-Hey, all!

07:14.935 --> 07:17.569
Gloria and I have been talking
about this for a while.

07:17.571 --> 07:20.405
What with Joe getting older,
I feel it's just the right time

07:20.407 --> 07:23.408
to start a new chapter,
which is why I've decided...

07:23.410 --> 07:24.409
To retire.

07:24.411 --> 07:25.877
-Oh, my.
-What?!

07:25.879 --> 07:27.546
[ All murmuring ]
Maybe "retired"
is the wrong word --

07:27.548 --> 07:28.814
more of a transition.

07:28.816 --> 07:31.049
So, when people ask,
"where's Jay pritchett?"

07:31.051 --> 07:32.717
You tell them,
"he's transitioning."

07:32.719 --> 07:34.719
-Mm.
-Okay, I heard it, too.

07:34.721 --> 07:36.555
Let's go back to retiring.

07:36.557 --> 07:38.256
Hey, we can finally
rent that r.V.

07:38.258 --> 07:40.091
And visit all
of the major league ballparks.

07:40.093 --> 07:41.593
You can probably go ahead
and do that alone.

07:41.595 --> 07:44.062
Uh, anyway,
I had to ask myself,

07:44.064 --> 07:46.264
"who's the best person
to lead the company?"

07:46.266 --> 07:49.167
And the answer is obvious.

07:49.169 --> 07:51.069
Chuck feeny.
-Who?

07:51.071 --> 07:54.005
Gutters and screen hot shot
out of Chicago.

07:54.007 --> 07:56.341
With him in charge,
we can all relax

07:56.343 --> 07:59.244
knowing that the company
is in good hands.

07:59.246 --> 08:00.946
Claire gets a great new boss.
-Mm-hmm.

08:00.948 --> 08:03.248
And you all get to spend
more time with yours truly.

08:03.250 --> 08:05.917
-Uh...
-Well, to this one's new boss.

08:05.919 --> 08:07.152
Uh...

08:07.154 --> 08:08.587
Claire,
that's my gesturing hand.

08:08.589 --> 08:10.021
I need it for work.

08:14.761 --> 08:16.261
I work 60-hour weeks
so Chuck feeny can have

08:16.263 --> 08:17.963
the corner office and
the best table at closet con!

08:17.965 --> 08:19.097
Honey,
you need to slow down.

08:19.099 --> 08:20.365
This coat
isn't quite broken in yet.

08:20.367 --> 08:23.301
Listen, you have
every right to be mad.

08:23.303 --> 08:25.303
Everyone knows
you deserve that job.

08:25.305 --> 08:27.339
And to think
of all the weekends I worked

08:27.341 --> 08:29.608
and the -- the family vacations
we've put off,

08:29.610 --> 08:32.010
not to mention the stress
and the insomnia and --

08:32.011 --> 08:33.979
-come here.
-[ Sighs ]

08:33.981 --> 08:37.616
Mm.
Claire, life's like
a Mountain road...

08:37.618 --> 08:40.552
With a new adventure
around every corner.

08:40.554 --> 08:43.020
If that's the slogan for this
stupid coat, I'm gonna kill you!

08:43.023 --> 08:44.322
Shh! Get in here.

08:44.324 --> 08:46.658
[ Sighs ]

08:46.660 --> 08:48.727
-Have you seen Claire?
-No.

08:48.729 --> 08:51.796
I told you this Chuck feeny
thing was a terrible idea!

08:51.798 --> 08:53.164
It's a brilliant idea.

08:53.166 --> 08:54.466
There is no Chuck feeny.

08:54.468 --> 08:57.002
I made him up because
of what happened to don McSorley

08:57.004 --> 08:59.204
when he turned his company
over to his son.

08:59.206 --> 09:02.307
Son only took the job
because he felt obligated.

09:02.309 --> 09:04.709
One year later,
business went bankrupt.

09:04.711 --> 09:08.580
Broke my heart to buy his entire
inventory 8 cents on the dollar.

09:08.582 --> 09:09.814
[ Chuckles ]

09:09.816 --> 09:10.982
I'm doing this for Claire.

09:10.984 --> 09:12.651
She'd do anything
to make me happy,

09:12.653 --> 09:14.886
and that's not why
I want her to take the job.

09:14.888 --> 09:16.655
If she wants it,
she'll fight for it.

09:16.657 --> 09:18.323
If not, I just gave her
an easy out.

09:18.325 --> 09:20.392
I can think
of 10 better ways to do this.

09:20.394 --> 09:21.927
Relax.
It's gonna be perfect.

09:21.929 --> 09:23.862
She'll come to me,
demand what's hers.

09:23.864 --> 09:26.331
I'll tell her the truth,
big hug, perfect Christmas.

09:26.333 --> 09:28.333
I'm a genius.
-You're a crazy person.

09:28.335 --> 09:31.002
In my village, we will tie
a tin can around your neck

09:31.004 --> 09:32.337
to know
when you're coming.

09:32.339 --> 09:33.405
[ Birds chirping ]

09:33.407 --> 09:35.006
[ Note plays ]

09:35.008 --> 09:38.510
Both: ♪ silent night ♪

09:38.512 --> 09:42.180
♪ holy night ♪

09:42.182 --> 09:45.417
♪ all is calm ♪

09:45.419 --> 09:49.187
♪ all is bright ♪

09:49.189 --> 09:54.426
[ Gratingly ] ♪ 'round yon
virgin mother and child! ♪

09:54.428 --> 09:55.860
Okay, hey, hey,
I have a fun idea!

09:55.862 --> 09:58.430
Why don't we give lily one
of her presents right now?

09:58.432 --> 10:00.799
-Ooh, that is a fun idea, daddy.
-Yeah.

10:00.801 --> 10:02.434
Then she can go play
with a toy

10:02.436 --> 10:04.970
rather than being
with us boring, old adults.
Mm.

10:04.972 --> 10:06.371
How's that sound, lily?

10:06.373 --> 10:08.573
I feel like you're up
to something, but I don't care.

10:08.575 --> 10:10.642
I want a present.
I'll take the bike-shaped one.

10:10.644 --> 10:12.811
Nice wrapping job,
by the way.

10:12.813 --> 10:14.212
Uh, wasn't that for Joe?

10:14.214 --> 10:16.715
-Well, Joe's getting a doll now.
-All right.

10:16.717 --> 10:18.216
[ Door opens ]

10:18.218 --> 10:19.217
Oh, hey.

10:19.219 --> 10:20.719
Hey.
[ Door closes ]

10:20.721 --> 10:22.921
Gloria asked me
to get some kindling.
Mm.

10:22.923 --> 10:25.490
Why are you walking around
wearing next to nothing?

10:25.492 --> 10:26.992
It's 26 celsius
out there.

10:26.994 --> 10:28.226
Ah, I'm not showing
any skin

10:28.228 --> 10:29.628
'cause I don't want
to tempt you.

10:29.630 --> 10:31.396
Oh, well, your gold blazer
took care of that.

10:31.398 --> 10:33.465
-You know you're into it.
-I know. Why?

10:33.467 --> 10:35.400
Damn you
and that eagle scout smile.

10:35.402 --> 10:37.569
I want to take a swim
in those big Doe eyes.

10:37.571 --> 10:39.004
This is happening.

10:39.006 --> 10:40.005
-[ Sighs ]
-Mm-hmm.

10:40.007 --> 10:41.806
-Getting wood, Andy?
-What?!

10:41.808 --> 10:44.409
Mm.
Can you believe Gloria
wants a traditional fire?

10:44.411 --> 10:45.910
As if it isn't hot enough
in here.

10:45.912 --> 10:47.245
-Mm.
-Come on, bro.

10:47.247 --> 10:48.813
Okay.

10:56.523 --> 10:57.856
Both: Hello, lily.

10:57.858 --> 10:59.190
What are you wearing?

10:59.192 --> 11:01.026
Mom made us put on
our Christmas sweaters,

11:01.028 --> 11:02.327
but look what we found.

11:02.329 --> 11:03.428
It's a note.

11:06.867 --> 11:09.267
"I'm hungry for the blood
of a little girl.

11:09.269 --> 11:11.369
Signed,
the forgotten boy."

11:11.371 --> 11:12.937
This is terrifying.

11:12.939 --> 11:14.305
It's getting real.

11:14.307 --> 11:17.509
The scariest thing is that
he spells like a 2-year-old.

11:17.511 --> 11:20.645
Wait, what?

11:20.647 --> 11:23.148
Dude.

11:23.150 --> 11:24.449
Christmas, huh?

11:24.451 --> 11:26.317
Who the hell came up
with this one?

11:26.319 --> 11:27.852
It was
emperor constantine.

11:27.854 --> 11:29.154
I love it!

11:29.156 --> 11:31.990
It's not easy being the smartest
person in the room.

11:31.992 --> 11:34.125
My sister thinks quantum theory
is a game show,

11:34.127 --> 11:35.226
and my brother once tried

11:35.228 --> 11:36.861
to take his pants off
over his head.

11:36.863 --> 11:39.464
Gals like us, we see through
all the family b.S.

11:39.466 --> 11:41.499
We call it
like we see it.

11:41.501 --> 11:43.368
So, if we're alone
for Christmas

11:43.370 --> 11:45.804
and birthdays and weekends,
it's their loss.

11:45.806 --> 11:49.040
Gals like us [Breathes heavily]
we don't need anyone.

11:49.042 --> 11:51.409
I'm not big on mysticism,
but, clearly,

11:51.411 --> 11:53.411
this woman was
my ghost of Christmas future.

11:53.413 --> 11:55.980
So, I decided
to turn things around

11:55.982 --> 11:58.483
and jump in
on the holiday spirit.

11:58.485 --> 12:00.351
Jump aboard the fun train!

12:00.353 --> 12:02.020
Whoo, whoo!

12:02.022 --> 12:05.323
That was a train.

12:05.325 --> 12:06.925
Something smells good!

12:06.927 --> 12:08.426
What?
What doesn't smell good?

12:08.428 --> 12:10.095
No, I-I said it did.

12:10.097 --> 12:12.063
I am confused!
What is it that you don't like?!

12:12.065 --> 12:14.599
I'm just excited for dinner.
I love you guys.

12:14.601 --> 12:16.601
Oh, don't be nasty.
We're trying our best.

12:19.506 --> 12:21.356
Yes!

12:21.357 --> 12:23.207
Hey, look what I found --
a key to that secret room.

12:23.210 --> 12:24.375
My entire family is here.

12:24.377 --> 12:26.377
Do you have any idea
how dangerous that is?

12:26.379 --> 12:27.812
Meet me in two minutes.

12:29.850 --> 12:31.382
There she is.

12:31.384 --> 12:33.518
Haven't seen you since
my big announcement.

12:33.520 --> 12:34.686
What do you think?

12:34.688 --> 12:36.721
I think that I gave my all
to this company

12:36.723 --> 12:39.124
and that if you were gonna
hand over the reins to somebody,

12:39.126 --> 12:42.026
it should be me
and not some hump from Chicago!

12:42.028 --> 12:43.695
Well, it just so happens --

12:43.697 --> 12:45.196
I'm not finished, dad!

12:45.198 --> 12:46.898
Thank you for saving me

12:46.900 --> 12:49.033
from wasting the next 20 years
of my life

12:49.035 --> 12:52.604
talking about slats,
rods, and hinges --

12:52.606 --> 12:54.305
from becoming
the most boring person

12:54.307 --> 12:56.574
in the most boring industry
on earth!

12:56.576 --> 12:57.809
-"Boring"?!
-Boring!

12:57.811 --> 13:01.479
Closets bring order
to a chaotic world!

13:01.481 --> 13:03.448
-What happened?
-I'll tell you what happened.

13:03.450 --> 13:05.216
I raised a mean,
ungrateful daughter,

13:05.218 --> 13:07.218
and I'm glad I gave the business
to Chuck feeny!

13:07.220 --> 13:09.387
There is no Chuck feeny!

13:09.389 --> 13:11.623
[ Birds chirping ]

13:15.295 --> 13:16.961
[ Thud ]

13:16.963 --> 13:19.898
[ Indistinct whispering ]

13:19.900 --> 13:21.733
Manny, Luke, knock it off!

13:21.735 --> 13:23.234
No one thinks it's funny!

13:23.236 --> 13:24.235
[ Rattling ]

13:24.237 --> 13:25.937
-Are you talking to us?
-Huh?

13:25.939 --> 13:27.939
[ Thud ]

13:27.941 --> 13:29.240
[ Wood creaks ]

13:29.242 --> 13:32.010
Hey, as long as everybody's
just sitting around, uh --

13:32.012 --> 13:33.344
oh, they're gonna
do another one!

13:33.346 --> 13:35.947
[ Indistinct shouting ]
Thank you, Santa claus!

13:35.949 --> 13:37.248
That's hilarious.

13:37.250 --> 13:38.750
Hope you're having fun,
'cause that's about to end.

13:38.752 --> 13:40.618
Okay, stick to the scripted
patter, sweetie.

13:40.620 --> 13:43.188
-Yeah, yeah, yeah.
-And a one and a two.

13:43.190 --> 13:45.957
Both: ♪ silent night ♪
[ Lily screams ]

13:45.959 --> 13:47.692
Oh, my God,
what was that?

13:47.694 --> 13:49.127
-Oh, I'm sure it's fine.
-Fine. It's no big deal.

13:49.129 --> 13:50.328
So, Mitchell,
here we go again.

13:50.330 --> 13:52.297
Both: ♪ silent night ♪
[ Lily screams ]

13:52.299 --> 13:54.766
That is your
daughter screaming!

13:54.768 --> 13:56.267
[ Sighs ]

13:56.269 --> 13:58.036
-Lily, are you okay?!
-What's going on?!

13:58.038 --> 14:00.605
The forgotten boy --
I heard him! He's in there!

14:00.607 --> 14:02.674
Of course he is.
All right,
let's get him out, huh?

14:02.676 --> 14:05.710
We'll make sure that
he doesn't bother -- oh, God!

14:05.712 --> 14:08.313
-[ Gasps ]
-Oh, God!

14:08.315 --> 14:09.981
Andy?

14:09.983 --> 14:12.050
Take off the blazer.
-[ Sighs ]

14:16.857 --> 14:18.623
We were just looking
for dinner napkins.

14:18.625 --> 14:19.624
Where?
In her shirt?

14:19.626 --> 14:21.459
I have
so many questions.

14:21.461 --> 14:23.461
Boys, lily,
go play where snow would be.

14:23.463 --> 14:25.129
So, is this a thing?

14:25.131 --> 14:26.664
Is it the first time?
-Yes!

14:26.666 --> 14:27.699
-No.
-Andy!

14:27.701 --> 14:29.734
I-I'm sick of the lies.

14:29.736 --> 14:31.870
We've been having
improper relations.
Oh.

14:31.872 --> 14:34.639
Aren't you engaged?
Oh, suddenly,
you're concerned about loyalty.

14:34.641 --> 14:36.207
Oh, you're talking to me.
Won't that bore you?

14:36.209 --> 14:38.409
Apparently, I'm boring!
-Listen, everyone,

14:38.411 --> 14:41.045
let's not let this ruin
our beautiful holiday.

14:41.047 --> 14:42.714
Alex, nobody needs
your sarcasm right now!

14:42.716 --> 14:44.048
It's ugly, honey.

14:44.050 --> 14:46.551
Cameron: This is Andy
and Haley's private business.

14:46.553 --> 14:49.354
I think we should be focused
on this special night.

14:49.356 --> 14:51.322
This special
<i> silent</i> night.

14:51.324 --> 14:52.690
-One and a two.
-No.

14:52.692 --> 14:55.093
Both:
♪ silent night ♪

14:55.095 --> 14:57.662
♪ hol-- ♪
guys, I have a surprise!

14:57.664 --> 15:00.231
It's Beth!

15:00.233 --> 15:01.599
Oh, my God.

15:01.601 --> 15:03.935
This is one
of my Christmas surprises.

15:03.937 --> 15:07.438
Andy, you can spend Christmas
with your fiancée after all!

15:07.440 --> 15:09.841
-Mmm, hi, bittle-battle!
-Hey, pumpkin!

15:09.843 --> 15:12.176
Beth, you mind if I have
a quick chitchat with your man?

15:12.178 --> 15:13.845
Yeah, I'll give Beth
a tour of the house

15:13.847 --> 15:15.546
while we get Gloria
up to speed.

15:15.548 --> 15:16.915
Don't you just love
the holidays?
Yeah.

15:16.917 --> 15:19.851
Full of wonder and magic
and surprise and --

15:19.853 --> 15:21.286
Gloria: What?!

15:21.288 --> 15:23.054
Sit.

15:23.056 --> 15:24.222
Mr. Dunphy, I am s--

15:24.224 --> 15:25.924
it's not your turn
to talk.

15:25.926 --> 15:28.192
That's my daughter, and you're
engaged to someone else.

15:28.194 --> 15:30.028
If this is a fling, it's over.
You understand me?

15:30.697 --> 15:33.197
But if this is something real,
you need to be honest with Beth.

15:33.199 --> 15:35.199
It's time to step up
and be a man.

15:35.201 --> 15:36.534
I understand.

15:36.536 --> 15:37.669
Let me tell you something.

15:38.538 --> 15:40.071
Life is like
a Mountain road

15:40.073 --> 15:42.106
with a new adventure
around every corner.

15:42.108 --> 15:44.208
-Wow.
-Right?

15:44.210 --> 15:47.045
-Did you just think of that?
-I did.

15:47.047 --> 15:49.147
[ Beethoven's
"moonlight sonata" plays ]

16:00.327 --> 16:01.993
Seems tense.

16:03.663 --> 16:06.331
Your big sis
is kind of a disaster, huh?

16:06.333 --> 16:09.667
Fig, we are a lot alike,
like you said.

16:09.669 --> 16:12.236
And sometimes
we can give off

16:12.238 --> 16:14.405
a negative vibe
without meaning to.

16:14.407 --> 16:18.242
What's your point?
Well, I was thinking
maybe we could make more

16:18.244 --> 16:22.747
of an effort to be more positive
and actually enjoy Christmas.

16:22.749 --> 16:23.815
As a goof?

16:24.985 --> 16:26.951
Okay, all right, new plan.

16:26.953 --> 16:30.254
We wait until the whole
haley/andy thing blows over.

16:30.256 --> 16:32.490
Everyone gets
a little liquored up.
Other people.

16:32.492 --> 16:35.593
And then, right before dessert,
you sit down at the piano.

16:35.595 --> 16:36.828
-Shh!
-You --

16:36.830 --> 16:39.130
Alex: ♪ silent night ♪
what the hell is that?

16:39.132 --> 16:42.433
Both: ♪ holy night ♪

16:42.435 --> 16:46.170
♪ all is calm ♪

16:46.172 --> 16:50.108
♪ all is bright ♪

16:50.110 --> 16:56.180
♪ 'round yon virgin mother
and child ♪

16:56.182 --> 16:58.316
-Son of a bitch!
-Mother...

16:58.318 --> 17:04.789
♪ Holy infant,
so tender and mild ♪

17:04.790 --> 17:10.728
♪ sleep in heavenly peace ♪

17:10.730 --> 17:12.896
That's it.
I'm drinking.

17:12.898 --> 17:19.404
♪ Sleep in heavenly peace ♪

17:19.406 --> 17:21.539
-Wow.
-Aww.

17:21.540 --> 17:24.041
[ Applause ]

17:24.044 --> 17:26.277
That's got to hurt!

17:29.816 --> 17:31.349
[ Sighs ]

17:31.351 --> 17:32.817
Hey, zucchini blossom!

17:32.819 --> 17:34.519
Hey, popcorn shrimp,
listen.

17:34.521 --> 17:37.588
Something is going on,
and...

17:37.590 --> 17:41.025
As painful as it may be,
I think we should talk about it.

17:41.027 --> 17:42.193
[ Sighs ]

17:42.195 --> 17:44.328
You could always
see through me.

17:44.330 --> 17:46.864
-What now?
-Yes, I met someone.

17:46.866 --> 17:49.333
I've been dating him for
a few months behind your back.

17:50.537 --> 17:52.103
And I'm actually
cheating on him, too.

17:52.105 --> 17:53.337
You mean with me?

17:53.339 --> 17:54.705
[ Laughing ] No!

17:54.707 --> 17:56.274
No.

17:56.276 --> 17:58.009
Oh.

17:58.011 --> 17:59.844
Popcorn shrimp.

17:59.846 --> 18:01.345
[ Wheels rolling ]

18:01.347 --> 18:03.181
Well, slight change of plans.

18:03.183 --> 18:04.615
I'm gonna be going.

18:04.617 --> 18:06.517
Merry Christmas, everyone.

18:06.519 --> 18:08.019
All: Bye, Beth!

18:08.021 --> 18:09.954
Drive safe!

18:09.956 --> 18:11.022
Keep in touch!

18:11.024 --> 18:12.557
I don't see us
keeping in touch.

18:12.559 --> 18:14.692
Hey,
you broke up with Beth?

18:14.694 --> 18:16.894
She cheated on me.
I can't believe it.

18:16.896 --> 18:19.297
-Wait, you're upset?
-Of course I'm upset.

18:19.299 --> 18:20.531
We dated for 10 years.

18:20.533 --> 18:22.366
I just got stabbed
in the back.

18:22.368 --> 18:24.569
-Welcome to the club.
-Really?

18:24.571 --> 18:25.970
You were stabbed
in the back?

18:25.972 --> 18:28.706
A daughter mocking
her father's life.

18:28.708 --> 18:31.409
Closets aren't fascinating?
Since when?

18:31.411 --> 18:33.211
[ Slurring ]
Want to talk about betrayal?

18:33.213 --> 18:35.246
How about when
somebody steals a song

18:35.248 --> 18:37.415
and takes it
for themselveses?

18:37.417 --> 18:39.784
I had no idea that you guys
were gonna sing that song.

18:39.786 --> 18:41.552
I did.
I heard them rehearsing.

18:41.554 --> 18:43.888
I thought there was an animal
stuck in the wall.

18:43.890 --> 18:46.124
And to think we invited you
into our home.

18:46.126 --> 18:47.758
We should've left you
out in the warm.

18:47.760 --> 18:49.727
Haley: I get that you're upset,
but remember,

18:49.729 --> 18:51.295
I even liked you
when you were fat.

18:51.297 --> 18:53.064
They give out awards
to people like me!

18:53.066 --> 18:55.733
I gave up
a three-day trip to cabo

18:55.735 --> 18:57.568
to close
that best Western deal.

18:57.570 --> 19:00.404
That's right.
You owe her 25 margaritas!

19:00.406 --> 19:01.906
-Phil!
-21!

19:01.908 --> 19:04.175
-21!
-Enough, enough, enough!

19:04.177 --> 19:06.077
All I wanted
was a white Christmas,

19:06.079 --> 19:08.079
and instead,
I'm back in Colombia --

19:08.081 --> 19:12.083
the heat, the betrayal,
people stealing songs!

19:12.085 --> 19:14.152
This ends now!

19:14.154 --> 19:18.256
Andy, stop whining and be
grateful that Haley likes you!

19:18.258 --> 19:21.692
She's a stone-cold 10,
and you're a Utah 7!

19:21.694 --> 19:26.164
Jay, it's time for you
and Claire to kiss and make up!

19:26.166 --> 19:27.932
Why doesn't he
kiss Chuck feeny?!

19:27.934 --> 19:29.634
Because there's
no Chuck feeny!

19:29.636 --> 19:31.769
He made it up to test you!

19:31.771 --> 19:34.939
And if she didn't care,
she wouldn't be this upset!

19:34.941 --> 19:36.941
There is no
Chuck feeny?

19:36.943 --> 19:40.478
It was a dumb idea, but I saw
what happened to don McSorley!

19:40.480 --> 19:41.846
The crackerjack
blinds guy.

19:41.848 --> 19:43.881
You got his whole company
for 8 cents on the dollar.

19:43.883 --> 19:45.850
I bought his photocopier
for 7 bucks.

19:45.852 --> 19:48.386
[ Chuckles ]
I always hoped
you'd take over the company.

19:48.388 --> 19:50.121
There's no one I trust
more than you.

19:50.123 --> 19:52.056
I just had to know
that you really wanted it!

19:52.058 --> 19:55.293
That I wanted to run a company
that gives people a place

19:55.295 --> 19:57.528
to store not only their jeans,
but their dreams?

19:57.530 --> 19:59.063
-Yes!
-Here.

19:59.065 --> 20:03.701
I got you a little
early Christmas present.

20:03.703 --> 20:05.970
"Claire Dunphy, c.E.O."

20:05.972 --> 20:07.004
-Oh, you!
-What?!

20:07.006 --> 20:08.739
Oh!
[ Squeals ]

20:08.741 --> 20:10.541
-That's more like it!
-[ Laughs ]

20:10.543 --> 20:12.410
Who cares
what the weather is?

20:12.412 --> 20:15.313
What is important is
that we have each other!

20:15.315 --> 20:17.315
[ Gasps ] Snow!

20:17.317 --> 20:20.651
Good king wenceslas,
there is snow!

20:20.653 --> 20:22.820
[ Gasps ]

20:22.822 --> 20:25.523
I told you everything
was going to work out.

20:25.525 --> 20:28.125
It's a perfect Christmas.

20:29.729 --> 20:31.896
-What are we looking at?
-Snow!

20:31.898 --> 20:34.332
Our miracle
for Christmas.

20:34.334 --> 20:35.399
That's not snow.

20:35.401 --> 20:37.668
That's ashes
from a forest fire.

20:37.670 --> 20:39.503
If you're quiet,
you can hear screaming.

20:46.012 --> 20:47.612
Phil, did you look
in all the drawers?

20:47.614 --> 20:49.280
Yep, and under the bed.
Got everything.

20:49.282 --> 20:52.583
-Bye, Gloria. Thank you.
-Bye.

20:52.585 --> 20:54.719
Jay, don't forget
Joe's new doll.

20:54.721 --> 20:58.089
Mitch and cam --
always pushing their agenda.

21:00.560 --> 21:02.093
Bye-bye, house!

21:02.095 --> 21:04.695
We will miss you!

21:07.934 --> 21:10.101
[ Ominous music plays ]

21:14.474 --> 21:16.240
Luke: Hello?

21:16.242 --> 21:17.475
Hello?!

21:17.477 --> 21:19.143
I-it's me -- Luke!

21:19.145 --> 21:21.212
[ Doorknob rattling ]
[ Sighs ]

21:21.214 --> 21:23.314
I think
I locked myself in here!

21:23.316 --> 21:25.316
[ Pounding ]
[ Pattering ]

21:25.318 --> 21:27.918
Uh, I don't think
I'm alone in here!

21:27.920 --> 21:28.986
[ Pounding resumes ]
